    <text type="letter">   
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc.01212.001_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <note type="editorial" place="top" resp="#ht">see notes July 2 1891<ptr target="loc.01212_n1"/></note>
            <opener>
                <salute>Walt Whitman,<ptr target="loc.01212_n2"/></salute> 
            </opener>
            <p>Be thou accursed,&#8212;who, calling thyself a poet, in the extremist tone of
                Vanity!&#8212;fail to recognize a poet&#8212;a bard, far greater than thou!!</p>
            <p><hi rend="underline">Yea</hi>! <hi rend="underline">Be thou</hi>, 
                <hi rend="underline">doubly accursed</hi>!!&#8212;for thy ignominious
                and dastardly attitude toward this loyal bard! So far above thee in <hi rend="underline">Love
                Greatness</hi><pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="loc.01212.002_large.jpg" type="verso"/>
                that, <choice><sic>thou</sic><corr>though</corr></choice> it seemeth must needs in gross pusillanimity assume to be totally
                oblivious of his Existence!!!</p>
            <p><hi rend="underline">Yea</hi>!! <hi rend="underline">Be thou trebly accursed</hi>!!!</p>
            <closer>
                <signed>Luther Carlyle Jr.</signed> 
            </closer>
            <pb xml:id="leaf002r" facs="loc.01212.003_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <pb xml:id="leaf002v" facs="loc.01212.004_large.jpg" type="verso"/>
        </body>
